here we will do cost-optimization project:
we will perform 2 things
first we will check if backup is attached to any volume if not then delete
second we will check if that backup is attached to volume but that volume is not attached to any ec2 then delete that backup as well.

For this we will create lambda function
The Lambda function fetches all EBS snapshots owned by the same account ('self') and also retrieves a list of active EC2 instances (running and stopped). For each snapshot, it checks if the associated volume (if exists) is not associated with any active instance. If it finds a stale snapshot, it deletes it, effectively optimizing storage costs.
